const e='---\ntitle: "Product Types & Fulfillment"\ndescription: "Learn about the 5 major product types supported by APayShop and their fulfillment logic"\n---\n\n# Product Types & Fulfillment Mechanism\n\nAPayShop is a full-scenario virtual trading engine. To meet the selling needs of different digital nomads, the system reuses the same `products` database table at the bottom level. Through the core field `type` combined with the `metaData` JSON extension, it implements 5 distinct product types and automatic fulfillment mechanisms.\n\nAll fulfillment (delivery) logic is unified and abstracted in the backend `server/utils/fulfillment.ts` engine.\n\n## 1. Key (`key`)\n\nSuitable for: **Game time cards, software activation codes, account passwords**.\n\n- **Mechanism**: The product needs to be associated with a "Key Pool (`cards` table)" in the backend. After a successful payment, the fulfillment engine automatically extracts a key record with `isUsed = false` from the corresponding pool, marks it as used, and displays it to the buyer.\n- **Out of Stock Handling**: If the key pool is out of stock (Sold Out), users can still place an order (unless anti-oversell limits are enabled), but the order status will enter `processing` after payment, prompting the administrator to manually restock.\n\n## 2. Digital File (`file`)\n\nSuitable for: **PDF e-books, cloud drive links, video tutorial archives**.\n\n- **Mechanism**: When creating a product, the administrator configures a fixed or dynamic file download link (Resource URL) or cloud drive extraction code in `metaData`.\n- **Fulfillment**: After successful payment, the order immediately changes to `delivered` status, and these hidden download links are displayed directly in the "Fulfillment Result" section of the order details page.\n\n## 3. Subscription (`subscription`)\n\nSuitable for: **SaaS monthly memberships, paid community access**.\n\n- **Mechanism**: This type of product represents an ongoing service status. The original `isPlan` field has been deprecated and is now completely taken over by `type=\'subscription\'`.\n- **Fulfillment**: After purchase, the order status directly changes to `active`. The valid period of the subscription (e.g., `1_month`, `1_year`, `lifetime`) is recorded in `metaData`, making it easy for third-party systems or administrators to determine if the user\'s rights have expired.\n\n## 4. Manual Service / Top-up (`service`)\n\nSuitable for: **Game boosting, server setup, non-standard services requiring buyer customization**.\n\n- **Mechanism**: This type relies on a powerful **Dynamic Form Engine**. When configuring the product in the backend, the administrator defines a JSON array in `metaData.form_schema` (e.g., requiring the buyer to input game server, character ID, server IP, etc.).\n- **Fulfillment**:\n  1. During checkout, the frontend automatically renders input fields based on `form_schema` for the buyer to fill out.\n  2. After payment, the order status enters `processing`.\n  3. The administrator sees the form data filled by the user in the backend order list. After performing manual delivery/top-up, they manually change the order status to `delivered` and can add delivery remarks to feedback to the buyer.\n\n## 5. Dynamic API Quota (`dynamic_api`)\n\nSuitable for: **AI interface aggregation sales, data query API call limit sales**.\n\n- **Mechanism**: Designed specifically for geek developers. When configuring the product, the administrator can set the `Quota` granted per purchase.\n- **Fulfillment**: After payment, the system automatically generates a unique `sk_...` secret key via underlying encryption algorithms, writes it to the `api_keys` asset table, and allocates the purchased quota. Users can immediately copy this API Key from the order and place it in the Authorization header of their code to call your system API.\n\n---\n\n> **💡 Developer Tip**\n>\n> If you are doing secondary development based on APayShop and need to add a brand new sales type (such as offline electronic ticket verification `event`), you only need to:\n>\n> 1. Add an enum to `products.type` in `schema.ts`.\n> 2. Add the corresponding `switch case` fulfillment logic in `server/utils/fulfillment.ts`. There is absolutely no need to modify the core payment flow.\n';export{e as default};
